Tron: Ares continues the franchise after Tron Legacy with Jared Leto (uh-oh), with not great results. People didn't and it became yet another box office flop costing Disney over a 100 million dollars. And while there are many reasons for that (like Jared Leto), the main issue is that the movie feels artificial. Fake. Not genuine. Not something anybody can really care about. So today, let's dive into why.
